{
  "text": "We start by presenting the taxonomy of NSWs from [CITATION_1] in Table 1. The taxonomy classifies NSWs into three broad categories: those that are largely alphabetic, those involving numbers, and miscellaneous instances, at least some of which do not fall neatly into either category. Within each category, a taxonomy is given that partly depends on the kind of operation that is involved in mapping from the input token to its verbalization; and partly on functional considerations of how the token is used.",
  "citation_candidates": [
